results.name: Number of total multiset partitions of the multiset of prime indices of n. Number of total factorizations of n.
comment: A total multiset partition of m is either m itself or a total multiset partition of a multiset partition of m that is neither minimal nor maximal.
a(n) depends only on the prime signature of n. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Dec 30 2019
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(product of n distinct primes) = A005121(n).
program: MultEulerT(u)={my(v=vector(#u)); v[1]=1; for(k=2, #u, forstep(j=#v\k*k, k, -k, my(i=j, e=0); while(i%k==0, i/=k; e++; v[j]+=binomial(e+u[k]-1, e)*v[i]))); v}
seq(n)={my(v=vector(n, i, isprime(i)), u=vector(n), m=logint(n,2)+1); for(r=1, m, u += v*sum(j=r, m, (-1)^(j-r)*binomial(j-1, r-1)); v=MultEulerT(v)); u[1]=1; u} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Dec 30 2019
